article.headline: Lipscomb 90, Tenn.-Martin 71
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Brandon Barnes scored 25 points and three Lipscomb players had double-doubles as the Bisons rallied from a 13-point deficit to defeat Tennessee-Martin 90-71 on Saturday. Adnan Hodzic had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Josh Slater added 15 points and 13 rebounds and Brandon Brown finished with 10 points and 11 rebounds. Trailing 39-26 with 2:55 left in the first half, Lipscomb (3-2) used a 37-11 run spanning 12:28 to take a commanding 63-50 lead en route to the Bisons' first road victory of the season. Lipscomb outshot the Skyhawks (2-4) in the second half, 56.8 percent (21 of 37) to 27.6 percent (8 of 29). The Bisons also had a 55-24 rebounding advantage. Jordan Burgason was 0 for 2 from 3-point range, snapping his nation-leading streak of 41 straight games with a 3-pointer. Benzor Simmons led Tennessee-Martin with 21 points and Mike Liabo added 18.
